{"name":"Deconstruct","type":"spell","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You distract the target with thoughts of introspective doubt and endless circular reasoning. The target must attempt a Will save. This spell normally requires 2 actions to cast, but you can instead cast it with 1 if your last action was to cast @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.3x6eUCm17n6ROzUa]{Crisis of Faith} against the same target. If so, use their Will save from @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.3x6eUCm17n6ROzUa]{Crisis of Faith} to resolve this spell, as well.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The target is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target takes 4 mental.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The target takes 4 persistent mental damage. While the mental damage persists, the target must spend its first action each round using Recall Knowledge, @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Seek]{Seek}, @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Sense Motive]{Sense Motive}, or a similar action that has the concentrate and secret traits and produces no physical result.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but increase the persistent mental damage by 4.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (+1)</strong> Increase the mental damage, persistent mental damage, and additional persistent mental damage by 1.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Frontiers of the Faith"},"rules":[],"slug":"deconstruct","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"traits":{"value":["fortune","mental"],"rarity":"uncommon"},"level":{"value":4},"spellType":{"value":"save"},"category":{"value":"focus"},"traditions":{"value":[]},"school":{"value":"enchantment"},"components":{"focus":false,"material":false,"somatic":true,"verbal":true},"materials":{"value":""},"target":{"value":"1 creature "},"range":{"value":"30 feet"},"area":null,"time":{"value":"1 to 2"},"duration":{"value":""},"damage":{"value":{"ScDLxhYGuPdPbCLK":{"value":"4","type":{"value":"mental","categories":[],"sub